refully in order to avoid a Canada visitor visa refusal. If you are applying for a temporary resident visa (TRV), you must provide a strong purpose of travel Canada visitor visa letter, or else you may get a rejection email with the following reason.<\/p>\n<p><strong>&#8220;I am not satisfied that you will leave Canada at the end of your stay, as stipulated in subsection 216(1) of the IRPR, based on the purpose of your visit&#8221;<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Tens of thousands of people visit Canada each year for different reasons. Some come to visit relatives or immerse themselves in Canadian culture. Others may intend to <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/work-permit-canada\/\">work temporarily<\/a><\/strong>. In either case, such individuals will need to apply for a visitor visa.<\/p>\n<p>Applicants who intend to apply for this visa will need to meet specific requirements and complete an application process. This application will also need to include a special <strong>\u201cStatement of Purpose\u201d<\/strong> letter.<\/p>\n<p>This guide will go over the requirements for this letter and also include a Purpose of Travel for Canada Visitor Visa Sample Letter to help demonstrate what the ideal letter should look like.[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;padding-6-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; centered_text=&#8221;true&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#822