21;regular&#8221; button_color_2=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; icon_family=&#8221;none&#8221; text=&#8221;Speak with an expert&#8221; url=&#8221;https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/contact-us\/&#8221; margin_top=&#8221;20px&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;What Does a Canadian Visa Officer Want to See in a Purpose of a Travel Letter?&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221; el_id=&#8221;get-a-job-offer&#8221;][vc_column_text]A Canadian visa officer typically wants to see that you have a valid reason to enter Canada, the funds to support your trip, that you are in good health, and that you intend to leave before your visa expires. A more detailed breakdown of the different things to include in your purpose or travel letter is described below.<\/p>\n<h3>1. Purpose of Your Trip<\/h3>\n<p>Your letter should directly state whether you intend to travel for work or recreation. You will need to be truthful regarding this, as the rest of your letter will include information that backs up this purpose. You should note that recreation can include any number of activities. This includes general tourism, attending events, or visiting relatives.<\/p>\n<h3>2. Your Reason for Choosing Canada<\/h3>\n<p>A Canadian visa officer will also be interested in knowing why you are choosing to visit Canada instead of other countries. If you intend to visit Canada as a tourist, you can mention your curiosity about visiting different Canadian cities. If you have planned to attend a wedding function or similar event hosted by your family or friends, you can mention this reason.<\/p>\n<h3>3. A Travel Itinerary<\/h3>\n<p>You will also have to include a detailed travel itinerary that answers:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>When do you intend to come to Canada?<\/li>\n<li>Which city do you intend to land in<\/li>\n<li>Where do you intend to stay?<\/li>\n<li>Are there any other cities you intend to visit or stay in?<\/li>\n<li>When do you intend to leave Canada?<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>4. Who Is Financing Your Travels<\/h3>\n<p>A Canadian visa officer will also need to see that you can finance your travels. Therefore, you should mention how much money you have in your bank account and how much you will bring with you. If someone else is financing your trip, you will need to mention this and ask them to provide proof.<\/p>\n<h3>5. Your Intention to Return to Your Country<\/h3>\n<p>You will also need to state that you intend to return to your home country once your trip is over. You can directly state the date you intend to leave Canada. However, you will also need to supplement this with additional reasons. This could include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Family ties in your home country<\/li>\n<li>A job or property\/assets you need to return to your home country<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>6. Details About Your Health<\/h3>\n<p>You should also include any relevant details about your health. For example, you can talk about any significant health conditions you suffer from or recent surgeries. You should also mention which COVID-19 vaccines you have received and the appropriate vaccination dates.<\/p>\n<h3>7. List of Documents<\/h3>\n<p>Lastly, you should list any documents you will be including with your temporary visa application. This includes:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identity document<\/li>\n<li>Proof of vaccination<\/li>\n<li>Bank statements<\/li>\n<li>A signed letter from the person inviting you to visit Canada (if applicable)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Related Post: <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/convert-visitor-visa-to-work-permit-canada\/\">Visitor Visa to Work Permit in Canada<\/a><\/strong>[\/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;The Purpose of Travel Canada Visitor Visa Sample Letter&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column_text]You can demonstrate that you will return to your home country with the help of the given Purpose of Travel for Canada Visitor Visa Sample Letter.[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner column_margin=&#8221;defa